HEADWORD: Tallyho
<hw>Tal"ly*ho`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>interj. & n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The huntsman's cry to incite or urge on his hounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tallyho coach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tallyho coach</b></col>, <cd>a pleasure coach. See under
<er>Coach</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

